DESCRIPTION:
	This file contains estimates of degree-1 gravity coefficients for the GRACE Release-06 data, 
	based on ocean and atmospheric models and GRACE coefficients for degrees 2 and higher. 
	The original method was developed by [Swenson et al., 2008], and subsequently expanded by 
	[Sun et al., 2016] to include the effects of the barystatic sea level fingerprint (i.e., 
        solving the sea level equation using land mass changes as measured by GRACE) in the ocean mass
	contribution to degree-1. 

	The implementation for degree-1 coefficients below uses the optimal parameter values as 
	described in [Sun et al., 2016]. These coefficients represent the degree 1 gravity 
	coefficients that should be added to the GSM coefficients to correct for geocenter motion, 
	relative to the modeled atmosphere and ocean degree 1 coefficients (e.g., GAC and GAD). The 
	coefficients have been normalized using the GRACE standards. Prior to the inversion for 
	degree-1, GRACE-C20 has been replaced with the SLR-C20 (TN-14), and GIA has been corrected 
	with ICE6G-D.

	To use for land applications or to compute global ocean mass, use these coefficients along 
	with GRACE GSM coefficients for degrees 2 and higher, along with a Degree 1 Love number 
	(k1) = 0.021.

	For ocean applications, add the degree 1 values found in the ocean bottom pressure product 
	(GAD) to these values. If you are interested in the full ocean, land, atmosphere geocenter, 
	add the degree 1 values of the atmosphere/ocean product (GAC) to these values. 

SPECIAL NOTES:
	1) Reported values are derived from geopotential anomalies relative to GGM05C (epoch: 2008-01-01)
		NOTE: A previous version from 04/2019 had an inconsistent epoch removed - please update all 
		      data with the most recent version
	2) The 1-sigma errors are based on Tab.1 of [Sun et al., 2016]
	3) The native GRACE & GRACE-FO C20 coefficient has been replaced with SLR-C20 (TN-14)
	4) GIA has been corrected for subtracting the ICE6G-D (Peltier et al., 2018) prior to the 
	   degree-1 inversion 
	5) From 06/2019 on, C30 in GRACE-FO has been replaced with SLR-C30 (TN-14)

FORMAT:
	The data format is similar to that for GSM, GAD, and GAC files distributed by PODAAC, see 
	GRACE Level-2 handbook for more information.
